The paper deals with the problem of private information retrieval (PIR) from non-replicated databases, which involves information theory, data structures, cryptography, and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves graph theory, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
